    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>25</citedRange>, with fig. 17</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#Sammelbuch"/> <citedRange>5879</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>009800</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#uhlenbrock1998"/>, p. <citedRange>107</citedRange>, fig. <citedRange>3</citedRange> (photograph)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#santucci-uhlenbrock2013"/>, pp. <citedRange>13-14</citedRange> and figg. <citedRange>9-10</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65999"><name nymRef="#Φιλοκρατεία">Φιλοκρατείας</name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tombe</supplied> de Philokrateia.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Burial place of</supplied> Philokrateia.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomba</supplied> di Philokrateia.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>مكان دفن فيلوكراتيا.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The placement of this inscription is a rare one. Usually the names are inscribed on the sarcophagus lid.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
